The evidence with the title 'The Price Of Public Money: the Presidential Election Campaign ... ' says May 27, 2016  ... In january 1976, the Republican governor of California had $43,497 to challenge incumbent president Gerald Ford, who had 15 times as much money. “if the challenger's campaign had not received $1 million in public money in january, and another $1.2 million in february, he could not have continued,” ... 
